Understood. You want to make the contact section span the full width of the screen while keeping the existing HTML and JavaScript code. You also want detailed comments for the CSS properties.

Here is the updated CSS to achieve that, with new comments explaining each property.

CSS
/*
 * Contact Section Styles
 * This CSS makes the contact form section full-width and adds a gradient background.
 */
.contact-section {
  /*
   * `width: 100vw;`
   * Sets the width of the element to 100% of the viewport width.
   * This ensures the section spans the entire screen horizontally.
   */
  width: 100vw;
  /*
   * `position: relative;`
   * Establishes a positioning context for absolutely positioned child elements.
   */
  position: relative;
  /*
   * `left: 50%;`
   * Moves the element 50% to the right from its normal position.
   */
  left: 50%;
  /*
   * `right: 50%;`
   * Moves the element 50% to the left from its normal position.
   */
  right: 50%;
  /*
   * `margin-left: -50vw;`
   * Pulls the element back to the left by 50% of the viewport width.
   * Combining `left: 50%` and `margin-left: -50vw` centers the element while
   * making it full-width, effectively negating the default container margins.
   */
  margin-left: -50vw;
  /*
   * `margin-right: -50vw;`
   * Pulls the element back to the right by 50% of the viewport width,
   * complementing the `margin-left` property to ensure full width.
   */
  margin-right: -50vw;
  /*
   * `background: linear-gradient(to bottom right, #f0f4ff, #ffffff);`
   * Applies a linear gradient background from the top-left to the bottom-right,
   * transitioning from a light blue (`#f0f4ff`) to white (`#ffffff`).
   */
  background: linear-gradient(to bottom right, #f0f4ff, #ffffff);
  /*
   * `padding: 80px 20px;`
   * Adds padding of 80 pixels to the top and bottom and 20 pixels to the left and right.
   */
  padding: 80px 20px;
}

/*
 * Contact Card Styles
 * This styles the main card containing the contact information and form.
 */
.contact-card {
  /*
   * `background: #fff;`
   * Sets the background color of the card to white.
   */
  background: #fff;
  /*
   * `border-radius: 16px;`
   * Rounds the corners of the card with a radius of 16 pixels.
   */
  border-radius: 16px;
  /*
   * `box-shadow: 0 12px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);`
   * Adds a subtle shadow to the card for a floating effect.
   * The shadow is offset by 12px on the Y-axis, has a 30px blur radius,
   * and is semi-transparent black (`rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08)`).
   */
  box-shadow: 0 12px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  /*
   * `padding: 40px;`
   * Adds internal spacing of 40 pixels on all sides within the card.
   */
  padding: 40px;
}

/*
 * Contact Information Text Styles
 * Styles for the text within the personal information column.
 */
.contact-info p,
.contact-info li {
  /*
   * `font-size: 16px;`
   * Sets the font size for paragraphs and list items to 16 pixels.
   */
  font-size: 16px;
  /*
   * `margin-bottom: 10px;`
   * Adds a bottom margin of 10 pixels to create vertical spacing between elements.
   */
  margin-bottom: 10px;
  /*
   * `color: #333;`
   * Sets the text color to a dark gray.
   */
  color: #333;
}

/*
 * Social Links List Styles
 * Removes default list styling for social links.
 */
.contact-info .social-links {
  /*
   * `list-style: none;`
   * Removes the bullet points or numbering from the list items.
   */
  list-style: none;
  /*
   * `padding-left: 0;`
   * Removes the default left padding that lists have.
   */
  padding-left: 0;
}

/*
 * Social Link Anchor Styles
 * Styles for the individual links within the social links list.
 */
.contact-info .social-links li a {
  /*
   * `text-decoration: none;`
   * Removes the underline from the links.
   */
  text-decoration: none;
  /*
   * `color: #1a237e;`
   * Sets the link color to a dark blue.
   */
  color: #1a237e;
  /*
   * `transition: 0.3s;`
   * Smooths the color and other property changes over a duration of 0.3 seconds
   * when the user interacts with the link (e.g., hovering).
   */
  transition: 0.3s;
}

/*
 * Social Link Hover Styles
 * Changes the style of the link when the mouse hovers over it.
 */
.contact-info .social-links li a:hover {
  /*
   * `text-decoration: underline;`
   * Adds an underline to the link on hover.
   */
  text-decoration: underline;
  /*
   * `color: #0d6efd;`
   * Changes the link color to a brighter blue on hover.
   */
  color: #0d6efd;
}

/*
 * Separator Line Styles
 * Styles for the vertical line that separates the two columns.
 */
.separator {
  /*
   * `border-left: 2px solid #ccc;`
   * Creates a solid, light gray border on the left side of the element.
   */
  border-left: 2px solid #ccc;
  /*
   * `height: 100%;`
   * Makes the height of the line 100% of its parent container.
   */
  height: 100%;
  /*
   * `width: 1px;`
   * Sets the width of the element to 1 pixel.
   */
  width: 1px;
}

/*
 * Responsive Adjustments for Mobile Devices
 * This media query applies styles when the screen width is 768 pixels or less.
 */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  /*
   * `display: none;`
   * Hides the separator line on smaller screens.
   */
  .separator {
    display: none;
  }

  /*
   * `padding: 20px;`
   * Reduces the internal padding of the contact card on smaller screens for better spacing.
   */
  .contact-card {
    padding: 20px;
  }

  /*
   * `padding: 0;`
   * Removes padding from the contact form and info columns on mobile,
   * allowing them to use the full width available within the card.
   */
  .contact-form,
  .contact-info {
    padding: 0;
  }
}

Explanation of Changes

To make the section full-width, I added these properties to the .contact-section class:

  • width: 100vw;: This sets the width to 100% of the viewport width, ensuring it takes up the entire screen's horizontal space.

  • position: relative;: This is a necessary step to allow for the next positioning adjustments.

  • left: 50%;, right: 50%;, margin-left: -50vw;, margin-right: -50vw;: This is a common CSS technique to create a full-width element within a container that has padding or a maximum width. It moves the element out from its normal flow to span the full viewport width.

All other CSS properties from your original code are kept and commented on in detail to explain their purpose. The HTML and JavaScript code remain exactly the same.

Just replace your old CSS with this updated version, and the contact section will now fill the entire screen width.
